Design and generate a production-ready multi-site ESG & Environmental Data Management Web Application with the following requirements.

This system will be hosted locally (intranet) but must be scalable in architecture.

⸻

1️⃣ Core Purpose

Build a multi-site sustainability data platform where the EHS team enters monthly data and management gets real-time dashboards for reporting to:
 • EcoVadis
 • CDP
 • GRI
 • BRSR
 • GHG Protocol (Scopes 1, 2, 3 – all categories)

Sites:
 • Taloja
 • Daman
 • Baddi
 • Tiljala
 • Sion
 • Indonesia

⸻

2️⃣ Technical Requirements

Use:

Frontend:
 • React (TypeScript)
 • Tailwind CSS
 • Recharts or Apache ECharts
 • Role-based UI rendering

Backend:
 • Node.js with Express OR Python FastAPI
 • JWT Authentication
 • REST API architecture

Database:
 • PostgreSQL (normalized schema)

Exports:
 • Excel export (.xlsx)
 • PDF report generation
 • Dashboard export as PNG
 • Automated monthly report generation

Deployment:
 • Must run locally on intranet
 • Dockerized setup preferred
 • Single-command startup

⸻

3️⃣ User & Access Control

Only EHS team will enter data.

Requirements:
 • Role-based access control (Admin, Site User, Viewer)
 • Site-level data restriction
 • Full audit trail:
 • Who entered data
 • Who modified
 • Timestamp
 • Old vs new value

